title: Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with 6GB RAM now available to pre-order in India
text:
Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with 6GB RAM now available to pre-order in... Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro with 6GB RAM now available to pre-order in India By February 10, 2017 “Samsung will start shipping the Galaxy C9 Pro in India from February 24th” 
Samsung launched its latest phablet dubbed the Galaxy C9 Pro in India on January 17th for Rs 36,900. The phone is finally available to pre-order on Samsung’s e-store. The brand will start shipping the handset starting February 24th. Samsung is also offering a one-time screen replacement for a period of 12 months for an additional charge of Rs 990. 
For the uninitiated, the Samsung Galaxy C9 Pro is the Korean giant’s first smartphone to boast 6GB of RAM. The phone flaunts an all-metal body, a fingerprint sensor and a 6-inch full HD Super AMOLED display. It comes with a Snapdragon 653 SoC, 64GB of expandable storage, 16MP front and rear cameras, 4G LTE, a USB Type-C port, NFC and a 4,000mAh battery. Facebook Comments
